{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.induct_roc_right\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">induct_roc_right</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">motive</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">base</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">step</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> (<span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>)</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Induction principle for proving properties of `Int`\\-based ranges of the form `a<...=b`\nby varying the upper bound\\.\n\nIn the `base` case, one proves that for any `a : Int` and `b : Int` with\n`b ≤ a`, the statement holds for the empty range `a<...=b`\\.\n\nIn the `step` case, one proves that for any `a : Int` and `b : Int`, if the\nstatement holds for `a<...=b`, it also holds for the larger range `a<...=(b + 1)`\\.\n\nThe following is an example reproving `length_toList_roc`\\.\n\n```\nexample (a b : Int) : (a<...=b).toList.length = (b - a).toNat := by\n  induction a, b using Int.induct_roc_right\n  case base =>\n    simp only [Int.toList_roc_eq_nil, List.length_nil, Int.zero_eq_toNat_sub_iff, *]\n  case step a b hle ih =>\n    rw [Int.toList_roc_eq_append (by omega),\n      List.length_append, List.length_singleton, Int.add_sub_cancel, ih]\n    omega\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.induct_roc_right","kind":"theorem","line":1638,"name":"Int.induct_roc_right","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.lean#L1638-L1665"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.induct_roc_left\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">induct_roc_left</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">motive</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">base</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">b</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">step</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> (<span class=\"fn\">a</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span>) <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">b</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">motive</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Induction principle for proving properties of `Int`\\-based ranges of the form `a<...=b`\nby varying the lower bound\\.\n\nIn the `base` case, one proves that for any `a : Int` and `b : Int` with\n`b ≤ a`, the statement holds for the empty range `a<...=b`\\.\n\nIn the `step` case, one proves that for any `a : Int` and `b : Int`, the\nstatement holds for nonempty ranges `a<...=b` if it holds for the smaller range\n`(a + 1)<...=b`\\.\n\nThe following is an example reproving `length_toList_roc`\\.\n\n```\nexample (a b : Int) : (a<...=b).toList.length = (b - a).toNat := by\n  induction a, b using Int.induct_roc_left\n  case base =>\n    simp only [Int.toList_roc_eq_nil, List.length_nil, Int.zero_eq_toNat_sub_iff, *]\n  case step =>\n    simp only [Int.toList_roc_eq_cons, List.length_cons, *]; omega\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.induct_roc_left","kind":"theorem","line":1610,"name":"Int.induct_roc_left","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.lean#L1610-L1636"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m </span><span class=\"fn\">n </span><span class=\"fn\">fallback</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span>).<a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int.toNat\">toNat</a></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span>&lt;...=<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Roc.toArray\">toArray</a></span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array.getD\">getD</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">fallback</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">fallback</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback","kind":"theorem","line":1605,"name":"Int.getD_toArray_roc_eq_fallback","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.lean#L1605-L1608"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.getD_toArray_roc_eq_add\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">getD_toArray_roc_eq_add</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m </span><span class=\"fn\">n </span><span class=\"fn\">fallback</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h</span> : <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span>).<a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int.toNat\">toNat</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span>&lt;...=<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Roc.toArray\">toArray</a></span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array.getD\">getD</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">fallback</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">i</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.getD_toArray_roc_eq_add","kind":"theorem","line":1600,"name":"Int.getD_toArray_roc_eq_add","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.lean#L1600-L1603"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/IntLemmas.html#Int.getD_toArray_roc\"><span class=\"name\">Int</span>.<span class=\"name\">getD_toArray_roc</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m </span><span class=\"fn\">n </span><span class=\"fn\">fallback</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span>&lt;...=<span class=\"fn\">n</span>)</span>.<a href=\"./Init/Data/Range/Polymorphic/Iterators.html#Std.Roc.toArray\">toArray</a></span>.<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array.getD\">getD</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">fallback</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ite\">if</a> <span class=\"fn\">i</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LT.lt\">&lt;</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HSub.hSub\">-</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</sp